---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const currentPath = '/about';
---

<Layout title="About GSTAT Index Generation Tool" description="This tool is free browser-based software for creating professional court document bundle primarily for GSTAT E-filing. Learn about the tool, its author, and how it helps lawyers and litigants.">
	<Header currentPath={currentPath} />

	<main class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50">
		<!-- About Section -->
		<section class="py-12">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">About GSTAT Index Generation Tool</h1>

				<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6">
					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						This tool does one job: Turning your documents into a proper GSTAT compliant court bundle.
					</p>

					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						GSTAT appeal checklist in questions 8 and 20 ask you to confirm if you have prepared proper indexing and bookmarking of documents as well as a single PDF containing all files. This tool helps to do both.
					</p>

					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						The current procedure is to use third party websites like ilovepdf for adding page numbering, then manually creating an index, then using the same software to split the files. This is VERY VERY time consuming and if a single page needs updating, everything has to be done again.
					</p>

					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						It's designed to be very quick and very simple so that anyone can use it even if they've never been near a court before, and to run in a browser (like Firefox, Edge, Safari or Chrome) without needing to install any special programs. The bundles are quite convenient, and work well for other contexts too - like formal meetings, for example. And it's <strong>totally private</strong>.
					</p>

					
				</div>

				

				<!-- Back to Home -->
				<div class="mt-12 text-center">
					<a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg shadow-sm transition">
						← Back to Home
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>

	<Footer />
</Layout>
